These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 3

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-1::.
There 4 different types of food: spinach, pineapple, grapes, cranberry
There are 4 different nationalities: french, american, chinese, argentine
1. the person eating cranberry is on the left of the person eating spinach##1
2. the person eating spinach is on the right of the person eating cranberry##1
3. the american is on the far left or far right##3
4. the person eating grapes is on the right of the chinese##1
5. the argentine is between the american and the chinese##2
6. the person eating cranberry is the french##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |     2     |    3    |    4     |
| Food   | cranberry | spinach     | grapes | pineapple |
| Nationality     | french     | chinese | argentine  | american      |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-2::.
The people have 4 different hobbies: photography, singing, traveling, puzzles
4 different pets are kept: hedgehog, fish, cat, guinea-pig
1. the person who's hobby is singing is on the left of the owner of the fish##1
2. the owner of the guinea-pig is on the far left or far right##3
3. the person who's hobby is puzzles is on the left of the owner of the guinea-pig##1
4. the owner of the guinea-pig is on the right of the owner of the fish##1
5. the person who's hobby is traveling is on the far right##1
6. the owner of the hedgehog is on the far left##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |     2      |     3      |   4   |
| Hobby   | photography | singing    | puzzles     | traveling  |
| Pet     | hedgehog    | cat | fish | guinea-pig |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-3::.
The people have 4 different jobs:  designer, mechanic, social-worker, writer
There are 4 different favourite beverages: sprite, lemonade, iced-tea, cola
1. the person drinking cola is on the left or right of the mechanic##3
2. the mechanic is on the far left##1
3. the person drinking iced-tea is on the left of the writer##1
4. the person drinking sprite is on the left or right of the designer##3
5. the person drinking iced-tea is on the right of the social-worker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |   2   |   3    |  4   |
| Job   | mechanic   | social-worker   | designer  | writer |
| Beverage           | lemonade | cola | iced-tea | sprite  |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-4::.
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: june, january, november, may
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: azalea, daisy, begonia, zinnia
1. the person who growszinnia is on the left of the person who's birthday is in november##1
2. the person who's birthday is in may is between the person who's birthday is in june and the person who growsbegonia##2
3. the person who's birthday is in may is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in november##3
4. the person who growsbegonia is on the left or right of the person who growszinnia##3
5. the person who's birthday is in june is on the right of the person who's birthday is in january##1
6. the person who growsazalea is on the right of the person who growsdaisy##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2      |    3    |    4     |
| Birthday         | january | june | may | november  |
| Flower   | daisy  | azalea   | zinnia  | begonia |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-5::.
There are 4 different favourite colors: azure, black, brown, grey
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: january, may, december, march
1. the person who's birthday is in may is on the far left##1
2. the person who likes brown is on the right of the person who likes black##1
3. the person who's birthday is in january is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in may##3
4. the person who likes black is on the right of the person who likes azure##1
5. the person who's birthday is in march is the person who likes grey##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |   1    |    2    |       3       |      4      |
| Color   | azure    | black   | brown | grey    |
| Birthday      | may | january | december       | march |

